originalText: The attack on the pirates has commenced. Our troops need assistance!
Do you wanna die!? This is a war zone!
Leave if you value your life.
Turn in your equipment and leave the island.
If you feel weak or experience a sudden burst of pain, report to the medical tent immediately. There are many potentially fatal diseases one can get here.
Keep your weapon ready at all times.
Always make sure your communicator is operational.
Chief Briggs does not like to be disturbed with frivolous matters.
The chief is right up ahead.
$(context.player.Name), get up - we have an emergency.
It ain't over till it's over. Keep your eyes open for a while longer, sec-trooper.
We have someone keeping an eye on the Lemurian at all times.
We maintained camp safety with minimal casualties.
This is the most difficult job Aegis Incorporated has ever done.
No activity from the natives. We must remain vigilant still, however.
We've lost Chief Briggs. We must act as though we haven't.
We must keep the expedition safe at all costs.
How many of these barbarians are out there?
No recent activity from the natives.
The pirates are no longer a threat to the expedition.
Many good sec-troopers were KIA during the attack on the pirate base.
Securing unlocked facilities will be a difficult task due to their locations.
No recent activity from the natives.
The pirates are no longer a threat to the expedition.
Many good sec-troopers were KIA during the attack on the pirate base.
Keep your eyes peeled. Danger lurks around every corner.
We are still waiting for the recovery team to return.
You are doing well for a mercenary.
The camp is not in danger of mutagen contamination, despite the rumors. Keep clear of the bodies brought from the Keep, however, as a precaution.
Always make sure your communicator is operational.
Keep your eyes peeled. Danger lurks around every corner.
No recent activity from the natives.
The pirates are no longer a threat to the expedition.
Keep your eyes peeled. Danger lurks around every corner.
The natives want us out at all costs. They'll strike again.
When driving a jet ski always keep a close eye for the sea serpents.
Always make sure your communicator is operational.
The pirates are still keeping their distance.
No recent activity from the natives.
The pirates are no longer a threat to the expedition.
We'll keep the area secured until the professor's been exctracted.
Locate the professor before the pirates regroup.
We haven't got time to waste!
Watch out, there are ships of war all around the island.
Protect the staff at all costs!
The researchers will arrive on first possible opportunity.
This area is now under Aegis Incorporated control.
This is an important historical site.
You are urged to leave the site as soon as possible.
Everything on the site is now Black Sea Expedition property.
Uhhh... can't a $(#man/woman) get some rest around here.
Aegis Incorporated has never lost a client. And never will.
We must not allow this to demoralize us. We have a client to save.
There's less than fifteen sec-troopers left.
We've lost many sec-troopers, but we made it through the ordeal.
We're down to a few sec-troopers.
The staff is beginning to notice the diminishing number of sec-troopers.
Our ammo supplies are running dangerously low.
We're running low on explosive ordnance.
Chief Briggs wants to see you. One of our teams encountered a group of hostile pirates in the evacuation tunnels beneath the Keep.
The professor has been kidnapped. The assailants moved in through the Keep's evacuation tunnels.
The pirates have been neutralized; we suffered no casualties. The chief is investigating the scene as we speak.
Kidnapped? Weren't there guards down there?
This keeps getting better and better...
What are we waiting for? Let's go after them!
Where exactly can I find him?
What does he need me for? Everything seems to be under control.
I'll go talk to him straight away.
We have yet to determine what exactly happened.
Chief Briggs is inside the Keep, at the entrance to the evacuation tunnels. You need to speak to him ASAP.
At the entrance to the evacuation tunnels, eastern section of the first floor below the surface.
Orders are orders, $(context.player.Name). See the chief.
